## Skin Prep: The Secret Weapon Behind Every Stunning Bridal Look

Here's the truth that every great makeup artist knows: **the canvas matters as much as the paint.**

The most luxurious products in the world can only do so much on skin that hasn't been properly prepared. That's why we dedicate a significant part of your consultation to your **pre-wedding skin prep plan.**

### Our Recommended Bridal Skincare Timeline:

**6 Months Out:**
- Begin a consistent skincare routine focused on hydration and barrier support
- Schedule your first professional facial
- Address any specific concerns (hyperpigmentation, texture, breakouts) with a dermatologist or licensed esthetician

**3 Months Out:**
- Introduce any targeted treatments (vitamin C serums, retinoids — but carefully, with professional guidance)
- Stay consistent with SPF daily — Fort Lauderdale sun is no joke
- Begin increasing water intake and clean up your nutrition

**1 Month Out:**
- Schedule a gentle, hydrating facial — nothing aggressive this close to the date
- Avoid introducing any new products
- Prioritize sleep and stress management (yes, this shows up on your skin)

**1 Week Out:**
- No new treatments, no waxing near the face (ideally)
- Deep hydration — face masks, serums, lots of water
- Light exfoliation only if your skin is accustomed to it

**Wedding Morning:**
- Use only your trusted, tried-and-true products
- Avoid heavy oils or moisturizers that can interfere with makeup adhesion (your artist will advise on specific recommendations)
- Arrive with clean, bare skin — let your artist take it from there

